message: Start by framing a single natural, soft item (e.g., flower, mushroom, sunflower) for 20 points. Use scissors on individual soft ingredients (e.g., thread, paper, cardboard) for 25 points. Combining two 'hard' items like 'beads' and 'shell' yields 30 points. The highest value item I found was by combining two 'cut, soft, artificial' items (e.g., cut thread + cut cardboard = 50 points). Crucially, never combine an item that has already been framed, as it will ruin the frame and result in a negative score. Also, be careful with using scissors multiple times on an item, especially complex or already cut ones, as it often drastically reduces value.
